## Remaining Work

### 1. Dependency upgrade is still incomplete

The current `frontend/package.json` is already converted from Angular to React/Vite, but it is still on the pre-upgrade versions:

- React 18 instead of React 19
- Vite 5 instead of Vite 8
- Vitest 2 instead of Vitest 4
- ESLint 9 instead of ESLint 10
- jsdom 25 instead of jsdom 29
- `@vitejs/plugin-react` 4 instead of 6

The migration plan still needs the actual version bump and verification run for the target versions described above.

### 2. Router/menu integration is still missing for new feature slices

The newly added `word` and `forbidden` pages exist under `frontend/src/features/*`, but they are not yet wired into the active router/menu. Current navigation still exposes only:

- `/home`
- `/import`
- `/domain`

The remaining integration work is:

- add `/word` and `/forbidden` routes to `frontend/src/app/router.jsx`
- add menu entries to `frontend/src/layouts/menuItems.js`
- confirm the new pages are reachable from the authenticated shell

### 3. Verification gates

After the dependency bump and route/menu wiring, re-run:

```bash
npm install
npm run build
npm test
```

If phase 2 or phase 3 of the migration is started later, re-run the same commands after each phase because the router and Tailwind changes can regress the app shell quickly.
